data.title: Boost Gauge
data.description: Designed and implemented a boost gauge for real-time monitoring of turbocharger performance in a car. The system accurately measures and displays manifold pressure, enhancing vehicle diagnostics and performance tuning.

data.title: Control Sims
data.description: Explore dynamic systems through simulations like a 1D Bouncing Ball, showcasing collision dynamics and energy transfer, and a Passive Walker, demonstrating natural stability and energy-efficient locomotion. These foundational models highlight principles of physics-based control and motion.

data.title: Lunar Architecture for Tree Traversal in-service-of Cable Exploration
data.description: LATTICE is a cable-based infrastructure that will enable robotic transport into and out of craters on the Moon. LATTICE targets implementation as the Moonâ€™s first scalable robotic infrastructure.

data.title: Rapidly-exploring Random Tree
data.description: This project involved implementing and simulating the Rapidly-Exploring Random Trees (RRT) algorithm for robotic path planning using ROS2. The focus was on enabling a robot to efficiently navigate complex environments by generating collision-free paths.

data.title: Tripteron
data.description: The Tripteron is a 3-axis parallel motion robot, similar in concept to a delta robot, but with all three input motions configured to be parallel to each other. This "Parallel Axis Tripteron" design leverages a simplified yet efficient kinematic structure for precise movement.

data.title: Stewards Platform
data.description: This project involved designing and implementing a stewards platform powered by Metal Gear Servos, utilizing kinematics and PID control for precise motion control.

data.title: Pupper: Robot Dog
data.description: Developed a quadruped robot heavily inspired by the Stanford model, featuring kinematics, control algorithms, and Python-based simulation and implementation.
